Police in Pittsburgh have described a neighbor of two sisters shot dead in their home earlier this month as 'a person of interest.'

The 43-year-old man, who has not been named, was questioned for 12 hours on Wednesday night as his home next door to that of murdered sisters Susan and Sarah Wolfe was searched.

Major Crimes Lieutenant Daniel Herrman said in a press release that the man is now considered a person of interest in the case.

