WPXI reports that sources close to the 
investigation said the man knew both of the women and 'certain 
behaviors' caught their attention, including being in possession of a pair of sweatpants belonging to one of the sisters.

The neighbor was released without charge to his apartment, one of three at 703 Chislett St in East Liberty.

'After the interview and subsequent search of the residence, detectives 
accompanied the male back to his residence. The male is considered a 
person of interest.'

Police have stood guard outside the residence since the man returned to his home.

However, Stephen A. Zappala Jr., Allegheny County district attorney, said the man was detained 'to facilitate the investigation.'

'It's premature to call him a suspect,' Zappala said.

